ITALY: Italy to abolish tax on CDs for non-residents.Italy to abolish tax on CDs for non-residents.Non-resident holders of Italian certificates of deposit will no longer be subject to a withholding tax from January 1 1997, Milan financial daily Il Sole 24 Ore reported on Tuesday.Following a recent shake-up of taxes on investment income, certificates of deposit held by Italian residents are now taxed at a rate of 27 percent.Italy announced earlier this year that the withholding tax for non-residents would be abolished from the beginning of next year on Italian government bonds, including treasury bills (BOTs), certificates (CCTs) and BTPs.Swiss inveastors will not be eligible for the tax exemption for legal reasons.-- Milan newsroom +392-66102321